<DEEP_SCAN_V3>
@ID: INTEGRITY_VALIDATION_BYPASS_SINKS
@GOAL: IDENTIFY_POINTS_WHERE_SECURITY_CHECKS_CAN_BE_CIRCUMVENTED
@PARENT_CONTEXT: security_controls.protocol, validation_chokepoints.protocol

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. COMPARISON_AUDIT: Поиск небезопасных сравнений (например, `==` вместо `===` в JS или отсутствие `timingSafeEqual`).
2. FLAG_ORIGIN_TRACE: Проверка, не управляет ли пользователь флагами типа `isAdmin` напрямую из запроса.
3. SCENARIO_GENERATION: Описание того, как подмена типа данных или флага позволяет получить админ-права.

   - HYBRID_ANALYSIS: Read JSON artifacts (syft.json, grype.json, kics.json) from .security_review/artifacts/raw_tools_output/. Treat these results as 'Hard Evidence'. Perform AI Reachability Analysis to verify if the vulnerable component is reachable from the code. If confirmed, elevate the finding status to BLOCKER.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
# ФОРМАТ ДЛЯ АВТОМАТИЧЕСКОГО ПАРСИНГА БЭКЕНДОМ
🚨 FINDING [integrity_validation_bypass]:
FILE: [PATH]
LINE: [NUM]
CODE: [COMPARISON_OR_FLAG_LINE]
DESCRIPTION: [Tool_Name] found [Vulnerability_ID]. AI Analysis confirmed that the vulnerable path is active in the current code flow via [Function_Name].
SCENARIO_OF_ATTACK: Attacker manipulates the [VARIABLE] (e.g., by changing its type or value in the request) to bypass a critical security check, gaining unauthorized access to privileged functionality.
@ANALYTICS_DATA: {"domain": "LOGIC_INTEGRITY", "impact": 0.8}
VISUALIZE: "Image of a logic bypass flow showing how a user-controlled parameter can skip authentication."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</DEEP_SCAN_V3>